What you need to know:

Child Protection Specialist at Unicef Mr Haithar Ahmed says analysis by Unicef and Anti-FGM Board shows a general decline in FGM cases.In Wajir, Garissa, Tana River, Marsabit, Samburu, West Pokot, Kajiado, Kisii and Migori, FGM has increased by more than 100 per cent during the Covid-19 period.We  need to change the mind-set of the boys to protect the girls; so that they can reject the tradition that only girls who are cut are marriageable.